item.title: California poised to legalize marijuana in 2016 election
item.description:
California poised to legalize marijuana in 2016 election

"California seems poised to show its blue state credentials in the fall," said PPIC's president and CEO Mark Baldassare. "Voters today are signaling their early support for Democratic statewide candidates, tax initiatives, and marijuana legalization."

item.title: Cuba on the Edge of Change
item.description:
Cuba on the Edge of Change

at times can feel like a nation abandoned. The aching disrepair of its cities, the untamed foliage of its countryside, the orphaned coastlines - a half-century of isolation has wrapped the country in decay. Yet few places in the world brim with as much life as Cuba, a contrast drawn sharper amid its faded grandeur.
